The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's emphasis on national sovereignty and human rights in his address to the United Nations General Assembly. President Trump believes that diverse nations should come together to protect their sovereignty and promote their prosperity. He also argues that national sovereignty is a moral imperative and essential for true democracy. The President's National Security Strategy highlights the importance of respecting human rights in advancing American influence abroad. The Trump Administration has used diplomacy, sanctions, and other tools to isolate states and leaders who violate human rights. President Trump believes in holding perpetrators of genocide and mass atrocities accountable for their crimes. He emphasizes the need to confront evil and not be bystanders to history.